postoperative values and, secondly, there are papers published in the literature 
showing that a difference of more than 12 points between the preoperative and 
postoperative scores in the WOMAC scale indicates a significant clinical 
improvement of patients.
CONCLUSION: Patients subjected to acetabular revision with a reinforcement ring 
together with cemented polyethylene have an improved quality of life after the 
surgical intervention.

